  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Types of Reasoning:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "**Inductive reasoning** — observing patterns, forming \n conjectures (not certain)",
        "**Deductive reasoning** — deriving conclusions from \n known facts (certain if valid)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Conditional Statements:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "**Conditional:** $p \\rightarrow q$ (\"If $p$, then $q$\")",
        "**Hypothesis:** $p$ (the \"if\" part)",
        "**Conclusion:** $q$ (the \"then\" part)",
        "**Converse:** $q \\rightarrow p$",
        "**Inverse:** $\\neg p \\rightarrow \\neg q$",
        "**Contrapositive:** $\\neg q \\rightarrow \\neg p$ (logically \n equivalent to original)",
        "**Biconditional:** $p \\leftrightarrow q$ (\"$p$ if and \n only if $q$\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Laws of Logic:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "**Law of Detachment:** If $p \\rightarrow q$ and $p$, then $q$",
        "**Law of Syllogism:** If $p \\rightarrow q$ and \n $q \\rightarrow r$, then $p \\rightarrow r$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Properties of Equality:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Reflexive, Symmetric, Transitive",
        "Addition, Subtraction, Multiplication, Division",
        "Substitution"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Properties of Congruence:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Reflexive: $\\overline{AB} \\cong \\overline{AB}$",
        "Symmetric: If $\\overline{AB} \\cong \\overline{CD}$, then \n $\\overline{CD} \\cong \\overline{AB}$",
        "Transitive: If $\\overline{AB} \\cong \\overline{CD}$ and \n $\\overline{CD} \\cong \\overline{EF}$, then $\\overline{AB} \\cong \\overline{EF}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Theorems Proved:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Vertical Angles Theorem",
        "Congruent Complements Theorem",
        "Congruent Supplements Theorem"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Proof Formats:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Two-column proof",
        "Paragraph proof",
        "Flow proof"
      ]
    },
